# MERN Ecommerce Environment Configuration

## Backend Environment Variables
# Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env and configure the values

## Frontend Configuration
# The frontend proxies API requests to the backend
# Default backend URL: http://localhost:5000

## MongoDB Setup
# Option 1: Local MongoDB
# Install MongoDB locally and use: mongodb://localhost:27017/ecommerce

# Option 2: MongoDB Atlas (Cloud)
# 1. Create a free account at https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
# 2. Create a cluster
# 3. Get your connection string
# 4. Replace in backend/.env: 
#    MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/ecommerce

## JWT Secret
# Generate a secure random string for production
# You can use: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"

## Port Configuration
# Backend runs on PORT specified in backend/.env (default: 5000)
# Frontend runs on port 3000 (React default)

## Development vs Production
# Set NODE_ENV=development for local development
# Set NODE_ENV=production for production deployment
